So ... PyData London 2018 was great!¶

  • 550 attendees (700 tickets between tutorials and main event)
  • 4 keynotes, 12 tutorials, 36 talks, lightning talks
  • 3 hackathons, Unconference, Diversity Round Table, Social Event + Pub Quiz
  • Beginners Bootcamp on Thursday (thanks Conrad!)
  • On-site Childcare support for the first time
  • Videos are on-line! https://www.youtube.com/user/PyDataTV

... and we raised $120,000 for NumFOCUS¶

  • Thanks to sponsors, speakers, reviewers, volunteers, attendees
  • NumFOCUS: a US-based 501(c)(3) public charity (https://www.numfocus.org/)
  • NumFOCUS supports open-source scientific computing projects
  • PyData: an educational program by NumFOCUS

  • Supported by PSF
  • 8-10 June (Fri sprints, Sat-Sun talks)
